              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">January 05, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1171</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Patel<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 21, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">An act to amend<font color="#B30000"><strike> Sections 87860, 87860.5, 87861, 87866, and</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Section</i></font> 87867 of,<font color="#B30000"><strike> to amend and renumber Section 87863 of, to amend, renumber, and add Section 87864 of, to repeal Section 87862 of, and to repeal</strike></font> and<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> to</i></font> add<font color="#B30000"><strike> Section 87868 of,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Sections 87867.5 and 87869 to,</i></font> the Education Code, relating to community colleges, and
		  making an appropriation therefor.</span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 1171, as amended, Patel.
                          Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law establishes the California Community Colleges, administered by the Board of Governors of the California Community Colleges, as one of the segments of public postsecondary education in the state. Existing law requires the board to appoint a chief executive officer, known as the Chancellor of the California Community Colleges. Existing law establishes community college districts throughout the state, under the administration of community college district governing boards, and authorizes these districts to provide instruction at the community college campuses they operate. Existing law establishes the Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance<font color="#B30000"><strike> Program</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Program,</i></font> which authorizes
			 the governing board of a community college district to provide a program of health insurance for part-time faculty, multidistrict part-time faculty, and their dependents.<font color="#B30000"><strike> Under existing law, a
			 multidistrict part-time faculty member who individually purchases health insurance benefits is eligible to participate in the program, and existing law requires a community college district to reimburse a multidistrict part-time faculty member for the district’s proportionate share of the total health insurance premium paid by the multidistrict part-time faculty member, as provided.</strike></font> Existing law requires the chancellor, by June 15 of each year, to apportion to each community college that establishes a program an amount that equals up to<font color="#B30000"><strike> one-half</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><font size="2"><sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub></font></i></font> of the total cost of the individual premiums required to be paid for the health insurance coverage of participating part-time faculty, multidistrict part-time faculty,
			 and their dependents,<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> and to apportion any remaining funds to each community college district that establishes a program and meets certain criteria, up to the total cost of the individual premiums required to be paid for the health insurance coverage of the participants,</i></font> as provided.<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> If funds appropriated for purposes of the program remain after those apportionments, existing law requires that the balance revert to the General Fund annually, as specified.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would<font color="#B30000"><strike> revise and recast the Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program to, among other things, additionally make a part-time faculty member who individually purchases health insurance benefits
			 eligible to participate in the program and require a community college district to reimburse a part-time faculty member for health insurance benefits purchased by the part-time faculty member, as specified. The bill would require the chancellor, on or before June 15 of each year, to apportion to each community college district an amount that equals the total cost of the reimbursements for part-time faculty, multidistrict part-time faculty, and their dependents, as provided. By imposing additional duties on community college districts, the bill would impose a state-mandated local program.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> instead require that the balance be deposited into the Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program Fund, which the bill would create. The bill would continuously appropriate the moneys in the fund to the chancellor for purposes of the above-described apportionments, as specified.</i></font></div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would<font color="#B30000"><strike> annually appropriate $200,000,000, on or before June 30 of each fiscal year, from the General Fund to the Board of Governors of the California Community Colleges for purposes of augmenting funds appropriated for part-time faculty health insurance.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
			 state the intent of the Legislature that, by January 1, 2030, each community college district commence negotiations with the exclusive representatives for part-time community college faculty to offer health insurance benefits to part-time and multidistrict part-time community college faculty and their eligible dependents.</i></font></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>The California Constitution requires the state to reimburse
			 local agencies and school districts for certain costs mandated by the state. Statutory provisions establish procedures for making that reimbursement.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>This bill would provide that, if the Commission on State Mandates determines that the bill contains costs mandated by the state, reimbursement for those costs shall be made pursuant to the statutory provisions noted above.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase"><font color="#B30000"><strike>YES</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>NO</i></font></span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.9104743117044718"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SECTION 1.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 87867 of the Education Code is amended to read:</i></font></div><div><div id="id_79101699-801F-4B38-A0EF-70277ED113F0"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">87867.</h6> (a) By June 15 of each year, the Chancellor of the California Community Colleges shall apportion to each community college district that establishes a program pursuant to this article an amount that equals up to one-half of the total cost of the individual premiums required to be paid for the health insurance coverage of participating part-time faculty, multidistrict part-time faculty, and their dependents in the district.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) By June 15 of each year, the chancellor shall apportion any remaining funds appropriated for this program to each community college district that establishes a program pursuant to this article and meets all of the following criteria, up to the total cost of the individual premiums required to be paid for the health insurance coverage of
						participating part-time faculty, multidistrict part-time faculty, and their dependents in the district:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) Offers health insurance coverage to all part-time faculty who meet the requirements in subdivision (c) of Section 87861.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) Offers part-time faculty the same health insurance benefits provided to the full-time faculty at the community college district.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Limits individual premiums paid by part-time faculty to no more than the actual individual premium paid by full-time faculty in that district.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) Offers health insurance coverage to all multidistrict part-time faculty who meet the requirements in subdivision (b) of Section 87861, and pursuant to Section 87865.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) The chancellor
						shall distribute funds that have been appropriated specifically for this purpose, and pursuant to subdivisions (a) and (b), proportionally based on each community college district’s total costs for premiums for those districts that submit verification of the costs of premiums for eligible employees for a fiscal year, but in no event shall the allocation to any district exceed the full cost of the verified premiums.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(d) If funds appropriated for this purpose remain after all apportionments for subdivisions (a) and (b) have been made, the balance that exceeds that amount shall<font color="#B30000"><strike> revert to</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> be deposited annually into</i></font> the<font color="#B30000"><strike> General Fund annually.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program Fund created pursuant to Section 87867.5.</i></font></div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s20.6524343703164851"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 2.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 87867.5 is added to the Education Code, to read:</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font><div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div id="id_7EC4CA85-203A-42AA-8F63-CABF756E6137"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">87867.5.</h6> The Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program Fund is hereby created in the State Treasury. Pursuant to subdivision (d) of Section 87867, funds remaining after all apportionments pursuant to subdivisions (a) and (b) of Section 87867 have been made shall be deposited into the fund. Notwithstanding Section 13340 of the Government Code, all moneys in the fund shall be continuously appropriated, without regard to fiscal year, to the chancellor for purposes of making the apportionments in subdivisions (a) and (b) of Section 87867 until reappropriated or reverted by the Legislature through the annual Budget Act or any other act.</div></p></div></div></i></font></div></div><div id="s30.9493922774499657"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 3.</i></font></h3> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>Section 87869 is added to the Education Code, to read:</i></font></div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font><div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div id="id_94442751-6EF3-4750-8F0D-D4FE595B9AD5"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">87869.</h6> It is the intent of the Legislature that, by January 1, 2030, each community college district commence negotiations with the exclusive representatives for part-time community college faculty to offer health insurance benefits to part-time and multidistrict part-time community college faculty and their eligible dependents.</div></p></div></div></i></font></div></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_1910C8A8-306E-428C-AE03-C77141D05C98"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SECTION 1.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87860.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87860 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_AD14871D-47C7-4DD0-8D4D-775DE63019F5"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87860.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_103D27CA-33C5-49B9-9A37-C89608B34965"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>It is the intent of the Legislature that part-time and multidistrict part-time community college faculty and their eligible dependents have continuous access to health insurance benefits.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_1FD2FE24-50F6-4AAA-9E09-DD787F9BCA71"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 2.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87860.5.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87860.5 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_7E928672-3E3A-4948-9970-C30EB6A0CA0E"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87860.5.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_1E127071-AFB0-428D-B35E-877A997CF879"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The Part-Time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program is hereby established for the purpose of providing state-mandated and state-funded health insurance benefits for part-time faculty and multidistrict part-time community college faculty.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_19E5D381-00CD-4123-89BC-9367E62D662A"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 3.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87861.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87861 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_A15B5F83-68A3-43F3-BACF-FB4127925375"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87861.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_44BFCE8D-6E6F-43DF-9587-9BDC1E3D0BC4"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>For purposes of this article:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Health insurance benefits” include medical benefits but do not include vision or dental benefits.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Multidistrict part-time faculty” refers to any faculty member whose total teaching assignments at two or more community college districts equals or exceeds 40 percent of the cumulative equivalent of a minimum full-time teaching assignment. “Multidistrict part-time faculty” does not include “part-time faculty” as defined in subdivision (c).</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Part-time faculty” refers to any faculty member whose teaching assignment equals or exceeds 40 percent
						of the cumulative equivalent of a minimum full-time teaching assignment.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Program” means the Part-time Community College Faculty Health Insurance Program established pursuant to this article.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_13254B26-FCBD-4F17-8362-C380CA54FE6E"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 4.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_REPEALED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87862.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87862 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is repealed.</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment/></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_8D6EF709-9285-4B68-8CAB-7CBB18941DFE"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 5.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED_AND_RENUMBERED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87863.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87863 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended and renumbered to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_40D14ECE-3827-4482-85A0-BE826F3DEAF0"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87862.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_2AF95EA7-BC60-4144-89F2-00BE0A9C8537"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>A part-time faculty member and their eligible dependents are eligible to participate in the program established pursuant to this article.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>A multidistrict part-time faculty member and their eligible dependents are eligible to participate in the program established pursuant to this article.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_31B99C54-C601-4475-BB79-4CC87A8C31CD"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 6.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED_AND_RENUMBERED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87864.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87864 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended and renumbered to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_29AE8D78-7264-490B-B25C-85772F0A5706"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87863.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_C0EC2FEE-01ED-4E7E-B3A5-AFEF717F06F8"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>A part-time faculty member, multidistrict part-time faculty member, or their dependents whose premiums for health insurance are paid by an employer other than a community college district are not eligible to participate in the program established pursuant to this article.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_E3871BA5-33C8-4A06-AD8C-FBCC1616B0BB"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 7.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87864.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87864 is added to the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName>, to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_05AD8E64-EAA0-4EB1-B418-131034639E39"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87864.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_EB0B2C33-2CF5-4C57-AD10-E1F88ED7A79B"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>A part-time faculty member who individually purchases health insurance benefits is eligible to participate in the program established pursuant to this article.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>A community college district shall reimburse a part-time faculty member for health insurance benefits purchased by the part-time faculty member. The reimbursement rate shall be 50 percent of the health insurance premium paid by the part-time faculty member, up to the full cost of the district’s most commonly subscribed family
						coverage plan.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>A community college district may require reasonable documentation from a part-time faculty member to determine the district’s reimbursement rate share, as described in subdivision (b), which may include, but is not limited to, documentation verifying enrollment in a health insurance plan and the premium paid for the health insurance plan.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_F8124500-F33B-4417-AB0E-9F07317C236E"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 8.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87866.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87866 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_2876A44D-5CE6-4A48-8AD4-438436B2582A"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87866.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_3E4CE3CC-6B91-4F3F-98AD-385919AD574E"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The governing board of each community college district shall, by June 1 of each year, send verification to the Chancellor of the California Community Colleges of the number of participants in the program.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_29FE00DD-7EF5-4283-AB28-D41D47FC1FD8"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 9.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_AMENDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87867.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87867 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is amended to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_F943FD56-C0E6-4DAA-B032-5831E1515F57"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87867.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_79424CDF-68C6-4520-9E15-00A7BEB7C151"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>By June 15 of each year, the Chancellor of the California Community Colleges shall apportion to each community college district an amount that equals the total cost of the reimbursements for part-time faculty, multidistrict part-time faculty, and their dependents as determined by Sections 87864 and 87865. </s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The
						chancellor shall distribute funds that have been appropriated specifically for this purpose, and pursuant to subdivision (a), proportionally based on each community college district’s total costs for
						reimbursements for those districts that submit verification of the costs of reimbursements for eligible employees for a fiscal year, but in no event shall the allocation to any district exceed the full cost of the verified reimbursements.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>If funds appropriated for this purpose remain after all apportionments for subdivision (a) have been made, the balance that exceeds that amount shall revert to the General Fund annually.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_C02E6CC3-12B1-4667-A9E6-E91DE7FAAE8B"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 10.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_REPEALED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87868.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87868 of the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName> is repealed.</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment/></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_A348DCFF-2726-4C42-8647-DE895CCBE8E7"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 11.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:EDC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'TITLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'7.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'51.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'CHAPTER'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'3.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'ARTICLE'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'9.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawSection%5Bcaml%3ANum%3D'87868.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SECTION" xlink:type="locator">Section 87868 is added to the <caml:DocName>Education Code</caml:DocName>, to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawSection id="id_64995E8C-B7E7-4D5A-B089-9B620C4F1DEC"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>87868.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_7FD2AA48-DD6D-4110-AB3E-0019A3F62F43"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The sum of two hundred million dollars ($200,000,000) shall be annually appropriated, on or before June 30 of each fiscal year, from the General Fund to the Board of Governors of the California Community Colleges for purposes of augmenting Schedule (12) of Item 6870-101-0001 of Section 2.00 of the Budget Act for each fiscal year.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_50AC12F1-C48D-4F30-AA85-6494A8165D5E"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 12.</caml:Num><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>If the Commission on State Mandates determines that this act contains costs mandated by the state, reimbursement to local agencies and school districts for those costs shall be made pursuant to Part 7 (commencing with Section 17500) of Division 4 of Title 2 of the Government Code.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:BillSection></strike></font></div></div></body></html>
